        "Name": "Svarog",
        "Details": "The Svarog, also known as the King Crab II, is named after the ancient Slavic god of fire. Unlike most other superheavy designs, it is intended to be a breakthrough 'Mech: it acts as the spearhead of an advance, engaging points of resistance and destroying them with massive firepower. The 4A deviates from the formula more drastically by mounting twin MRM 40s and a pair of RAC2s, the flamers having been replaced with lighter ER Small Lasers for weight savings. The Svarog has proved to be quite successful; even if an overconfident MechWarrior outruns their support, the 'Mech's sheer firepower and protection mean it can survive against heavy odds until help arrives.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
